		<article id="comment-203" class="comment-body clearfix">
			<div class="comment_avatar">
				<img alt='Cristina Luisa' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/bf5146f468a99584d99a730a56782982?s=80&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/bf5146f468a99584d99a730a56782982?s=160&amp;d=monsterid&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' />			</div>

			<div class="comment_postinfo">
				<span class="fn"><a href='http://www.chroniclesofatraveladdict.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Cristina Luisa</a></span>				<span class="comment_date">
				on 29 February, 2016 at 8:03 am				</span>
										</div> <!-- .comment_postinfo -->

			<div class="comment_area">
				
				<div class="comment-content clearfix">
				<p>This is a very important topic that is seldom discussed. I have been the victim and almost-victim of sexual harassment while traveling abroad. It&#8217;s hard to know exactly what to do, according to local social norms, but my advice is to protect yourself no matter what locals do. If you feel uncomfortable, then it&#8217;s not cool. I agree with carrying pepper spray. In more dangerous countries, I carry a knife. I&#8217;d also suggest that ALL females take self-defense or martial arts classes, whether or not you plan to travel alone. Knowing how to protect myself not only makes me feel more confident, but it has also stopped what could have been a rape.</p>
				</div> <!-- end comment-content-->
			</div> <!-- end comment_area-->
		</article> <!-- .comment-body -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 et-pb-non-builder-comment" id="li-comment-201">
		<article id="comment-201" class="comment-body clearfix">
			<div class="comment_avatar">
				<img alt='goblinette' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/c9a111f4ce19949d400d5abab266f32e?s=80&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/c9a111f4ce19949d400d5abab266f32e?s=160&amp;d=monsterid&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' />			</div>

			<div class="comment_postinfo">
				<span class="fn"><a href='http://www.roaminggoblin.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>goblinette</a></span>				<span class="comment_date">
				on 29 February, 2016 at 6:01 am				</span>
										</div> <!-- .comment_postinfo -->

			<div class="comment_area">
				
				<div class="comment-content clearfix">
				<p>I love reading a useful article once in a while. I somehow attract all kinds of perverts when I travel alone. Probably, because I look younger than I really am. That is why I prefer to travel with a friend or partner. And when I travel alone, I avoid dark alleys and places that are not full of other people and don’t drink any alcohol. I miss some fun things because of that, but I haven’t had any really problematic encounters in a few years.</p>
				</div> <!-- end comment-content-->
			</div> <!-- end comment_area-->
